Create React App:

Steps:
1. Install node npm
2. npm install -g create-react-app
3. npm init react-app my-app

For more details please visit below link:
https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app

Babel and Presets , Webpack -  we are using for budling code and convert ES6 to ES5

manifest.json - used for progessive web apps/ gives metadata about our project

registerServiceWorker.js - Used for progessive web apps and used to cache script files.

Public -- > index.html starting of application

index.js - Renders application on browser using React.Dom.render

Working with Components:
ReactDom.render(<h1>Test</h1>,document.getElementById('root'));
one root component(App.js) - then nest your children components.

Ways of defining components:
1.class component
2.functional component

JSX:
className - class

why need to import react?
React.createElement

JSX restrictions:
-JSX must have one root element


“Props” is a special keyword in React, which stands for properties 
and is being used for passing data from one component to another. 
But the important part here is that data with props are being passed in a uni-directional flow.